## Quick start

```bash
make launch          # idempotent re-run of bootstrap
make validate-launch # run deterministic validation
make okf-validate    # validate OKF context bundle
make mcp-health      # verify MCP server reachability
make mcp-register    # register this project with MCP
make worker-next     # dispatch first ready backlog task to worker
make worker-status   # inspect running/completed worker state
make review-runs     # summarize latest worker manifests
```

## Worker quick reference

- Default routing uses task metadata (`agent_hint`, `required_skills`), then `WORKER_DEFAULT_AGENT` (default: `codex`).
- Set worker binaries with `WORKER_CODEX_BIN` / `WORKER_CLAUDE_BIN`.
- Optional command allowlist: `WORKER_COMMAND_ALLOWLIST=/abs/path/codex,/abs/path/claude`.
- Concurrency controls: `WORKER_MAX_GLOBAL` and `WORKER_MAX_PER_AGENT`.
- Safe smoke path (no real agent CLI needed): `WORKER_CODEX_BIN=true make worker-start TASK=TASK-0001`.

## Layout

- `scripts/` - launcher, GitHub bootstrap, validation
- `scripts/mcp/` - MCP wrapper scripts
- `.okf/` - curated project context, decisions, risks, handoffs, improvements
- `schemas/` - JSON Schemas for backlog, evidence, audit, errors
- `backlog/` - task specs and queue
- `docs/` - operating model, runbook, governance, security

